    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, our offensive engine is centered on high-ceiling matchups against soft-tossing right-handers. **Tyler Soderstrom** (76.91) and **Vinnie Pasquantino** (76.21) emerge as our top starts, both buoyed by favorable park factors and the exploitable 4.47 and 4.43 xERA marks of their respective opponents. **Mickey Moniak** (75.75) is equally compelling; his matchup against Ryan Weiss\u2014a pitcher with a vulnerable 7.36 xERA\u2014allows him to capitalize on his elite sprint speed and a prime #2 spot in the order. We are also leaning heavily into **Josh Naylor** (74.81), whose ability to punish a struggling Walker Buehler makes him our most bankable utility play, even with a lineup designation that remains pending.\n\nWe have aggressive exposure to the favorable conditions surrounding the Suter matchup. **Giancarlo Stanton** (64.21) and **Jose Caballero** (66.69) benefit significantly from wind blowing out and specific platoon edges, with **Jose Caballero** seeing a +13% boost due to his platoon profile. Meanwhile, **Brice Turang** (63.08) remains a critical cornerstone of our strategy; while his raw power is modest, his 63-point efficiency score is driven by his elite base-stealing potential against a slow-delivering Patrick Corbin. The tightest call on the board was **Max Muncy** (59.76), who narrowly held his spot in the lineup over our secondary depth pieces. He was favored over prospects like **Dalton Rushing** or **Travis Bazzana** due to the park factors and the slight stolen base upside afforded by the opposing pitcher's delivery speed, despite the risk associated with his current #7 lineup slot.\n\nWe are navigating a few \"Lineup Pending\" designations today, notably for **Luis Campusano** (43.78) and **Kyle Karros** (50.77). **Luis Campusano** represents our lowest-scoring start of the day; he is barely clearing our 40-point \"Below floor\" threshold, and we are only deploying him to maintain our game caps while we wait for more consistent production from the catching position. We are monitoring the status of **Gabriel Moreno** and **Alex Freeland** closely, as any shift in the starting order could necessitate a pivot to prevent wasted plate appearances. With **Corbin Carroll**, **Austin Riley**, **Seiya Suzuki**, and **Trevor Story** all sitting due to team off-days, our bench remains stagnant, placing the burden of production squarely on the shoulders of our active starters to sustain our Roto standing.",
